definition: to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
to leave/to depart/to separate/to distinguish/to classify/other/another/don't ...!/to pin/to stick (sth) in
to make sb change their ways, opinions etc

sentences.english: His height distinguishes him from the other boys.
sentences.chinese: 他的身高使他有别于其他男孩。

sentences.english: But unlike evolution in biology, we know exactly what’s going on.
sentences.chinese: 但有别于生物进化的是，我们确切知道其进程。

sentences.english: But, the exhibition also has its particularity, apart from other circulation medium.
sentences.chinese: 但是，展览也有其特殊性，有别于其他流通媒介。

sentences.english: A new method, which is different from the traditional one, is used to set upLebesgue integral.
sentences.chinese: 用有别于传统的方法建立了勒贝格积分。

sentences.english: Researchers has found that the benefits of taking aspirin regularly differs between men and women.
sentences.chinese: 研究人员发现阿司匹林的药效男女有别。

sentences.english: HOT TYPE Foundry type and linecaster slugs as opposed to cold type.
sentences.chinese: 铸造的活字和整行的铅字条，有别于冷式字。

sentences.english: Engineering and technology are disciplines distinct from one another and from science.
sentences.chinese: 工程学和工艺学互不相同，也有别于自然学科。

sentences.english: I say I am yet too young to understand that God is any respecter of persons.
sentences.chinese: 我说，我还是太年轻，无法理解上帝会待人有别。

sentences.english: This distinguished syntax from phonology and semantics.
sentences.chinese: 这使句法学有别于音位学和语义学。

sentences.english: The basic idea in content analysis can be considered independently of a community approach.
sentences.chinese: 内容分析的基本思想有别于社区方式。

sentences.english: Her red hair distinguished her from her sisters.
sentences.chinese: 她的红头发使她有别于她的姐妹们。

sentences.english: The law English is an instrumental language which is quite distinct from ordinary English.
sentences.chinese: 法律英语是一门有别于普通英语的工具性语言。

sentences.english: What separated Christine from the other applicants was her years of experience.
sentences.chinese: 使克里斯廷有别于其它应征者的是她多年的经验。

sentences.english: Fresh cheese is not aged before eating.
sentences.chinese: 所谓新鲜乳酪，就是在食用前有别于陈年品种的乳酪。

sentences.english: In social development's different time, the development concept also displays far is able to discriminate.
sentences.chinese: 在社会发展的不同时期，发展观也表现得迥然有别。

definition: other/the others/else/other than it/in addition to the thing mentioned above
difference/to distinguish/to discriminate/to make a distinction/CL:個|个[ge4]
to be born/(fig.) to develop out of sth else (of ideas, stories, political systems etc)/(fig.) to shed one's body (to be reborn)/bodiless (e.g. lacquerware)
virtually the same/differing only on small points
to limit/to confine/to restrict sth within set boundaries
partial towards sth/to prefer/to incline/erroneous tendencies (Leftist or Revisionist deviation)
